    "type": "mcq",
    "text": "Three point charges $+q$, $-q$, and $+q$ are placed at the vertices of an equilateral triangle of side $a$. The potential energy of the system is:",
    "image": "",
    "options": [
      { "text": "$\\dfrac{-kq^2}{a}$", "image": "" },
      { "text": "$\\dfrac{-kq^2}{3a}$", "image": "" },
      { "text": "$0$", "image": "" },
      { "text": "$\\dfrac{kq^2}{a}$", "image": "" }
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Potential energy = $k\\left[\\frac{(+q)(-q)}{a} + \\frac{(+q)(+q)}{a} + \\frac{(-q)(+q)}{a}\\right]$\n$$= \\frac{k}{a}[-q^2 + q^2 - q^2] = \\frac{-kq^2}{a}$$"
